main event: A civilian observed three unidentified objects over Minneapolis, Minnesota, for one hour on November 20, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as pale blue, red, and white lights,The sighting was reported by three witnesses,The duration of the observation was one hour,The objects appeared to be stationary for the duration of the observation,There was no physical evidence or photographs taken during the sighting.
sighted object: three unidentified lights in the sky
witness description: civilians including a music teacher and a computer programmer
